The paper presents a robot system that follows human natural language instructions to pick and place everyday objects, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The core issue addressed in the paper is the grounding of referring expressions, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed approach uses neural networks for grounding and question generation, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO, followed by cs.CL and cs.CV, and then cs.AI and cs.LG.
